</head><body><table width=90% align=center><tr><td class=textbody><center><h1>Lvl 55-60: The Scarlet Desert</h1><br>by Shafli Tritium</center><br><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="border-collapse: collapse" bordercolor="#111111" width="531" id="AutoNumber1">
  <tr>
    <td width="531"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: Verdana">
    <font color="#FFFFFF"><b>55-60, Scarlet Desert</b></font><br>
    Minimum Level: 55<br>
    Maximum Level: 60<br>
    Zone Name: Scarlet Desert<br>
    Camp Area/LOC: Mesa<br>
    Mob List (HP): Tro Jeg, Reverants<br>
    Availability (1-&gt;10): 8 (frequently open)<br>
    Loot Ranking (1-&gt;10): 5 <br>
    Diff.Ranking (1-&gt;10): 4 (learning curve, then easy)<br>
    Faction Affected: none<br>
    <br>
    Other Notes/Tips/Warnings: There are 2 viable mob types that can easily be 
    quadded here, Tro Jeg and Reverants. The main place is a mesa in the 
    northern part of the zone. On top of the mesa are a decayed castle and a 
    small temple. <br>
    <br>
    When kiting the Tro Jeg I pull with snare then gather them and resnare. Kite 
    along the edge of the mesa. Warders are casters and need to be pulled as 
    singles. <br>
    <br>
    Same thing when kiting the Reverants except the Reavers are casters and need 
    to be single pulled. <br>
    <br>
    Camps are frequently open; kite is very, very, very easy. Experience is good 
    up to level 60. At level 61 things start to go light blue and green. <br>
    <![if !supportLineBreakNewLine]><br>
